text.section:
Before the license or certificate expires, the licensee or certificate holder periodically may renew it for an additional 2-year term, if the licensee or certificate holder:
Otherwise is entitled to be licensed or certified;
Pays to the Board the renewal fee set by the Board;
Submits to the Board a renewal application on the form that the Board requires; and
Submits satisfactory evidence of compliance with any continuing education requirements as required by the Board for license or certificate renewal.
